The Florida Motor Vehicle Licensing and Testing center west of Johannesburg was on Monday robbed of an undisclosed amount of cash. Police say criminals held up two security guards who were on duty, assaulted them before tying them up. A loud explosion was heard before the gang fled the scene with an undisclosed amount of cash. Gauteng police spokesperson Kay Makhubele said, “We understand that an undisclosed amount of cash was stolen as well as other items. We are calling on anyone with information to come forward. The security guards have been injured they’ve been taken to hospital, but arrests have been made yet.” 